Americans who plan to mark today's National Peanut Butter and Jelly Day with a celebratory sandwich should be prepared to pay more for the sweet treat than in years past.

As data from the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics shows, price of two of the main ingredients that go into making an old-fashioned PB&J sandwich - peanut butter and white butter - have skyrocketed since 2004.  

The price of a pound of creamy peanut butter jumped from $1.85 to $2.7 in a decade - a spike of 46 per cent.

