At the same time, the cost of white bread increased by 47 per cent, rising from 95 cents in 2004 to $1.36 in January 2014.  

And for those adventurous eaters who enjoy mixing things up with a sliced banana in their PB&J sandwich, the snack will cost even more.

According to the Bureau of Labor Statistics, the price of bananas has gone from 52 cents a pound in 2004 to just under 60 cents in February 2014. 

CNBC reported that when all is said and done, the combined increases in cost amount to less than $1 per sandwich, but nickels and dimes quickly add up considering how much PB&J is consumed in the U.S. in a single a year.

